But if the organisers’ master plan comes to pass the big Junkers won’t be the largest aircraft at Goodwood. It seems unbelievable that the massive Lockheed C-130 Hercules can land on Goodwood’s grass runways, but the RAF has been over for a pitch inspection and says that it’s possible. We must cross our fingers that it’ll happen because that aircraft will be some sight. And just in case you were wondering, yes the Herc does comply with Goodwood’s 1966 cut-off rule.
